title: Wasim Qadir wins NA-121 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Wasim Qadir has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-121 Lahore-V by securing 78,703 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Sheikh Rohail Asghar of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz, who bagged 70,597 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 40.08 percent.
